column5: And you even kept your shirt on, how civilized.  Cool G  Joey
3 nice gentlemen from Canada and Glenn gets his picture? Taking care of the home boy? If we can`t see Canada at least show Canadians?
WOW, looks like a good time had by all...
Looking forward to the report Bubba. Brian looks a little green around the gills there.
Way to go GCD! I wonder why they call them 'Trigger' Fish?

they can erect the first two dorsal spines, the first one locks and the second one unlocks. It keeps larger fish from swallowing them.  GCD you are a fish tease!! That is a real nice jack you got there .
ok Dawg, you've had long enough....where's the real deal ???   Glad y'all had a great time  Maureen
Wait a go Dawg !!!!! Looks like some sweet weather down there for October but then again we have been expereincing some mild tempretures for this time of year here in the north as well.....
WTG Dawg!!! Wish i could get half the fishin in that you do im jealous!!!
I'd go for some of that.
Very nice, Glen.  Looking forward to your report!  We be fixin to get some BoQ walleyes as big as them.
